@node "Introduction" "Introduction to Idle A68K"
@next "Introduction"
@prev "Introduction"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Idle A68K@{ub} is an @{u}instrument@{uu} to see how busy the system is. Nothing more, nothing less.
There are a couple of other programs who do the same thing, so what's the difference?
Try it out! Start this program together with another one. You should see it now.
The others say the system is 100% busy, but it's not ! This happens to MOST of them, not all.
This makes virtually all of them worthless for real debugging. That was exactly my aim, to make
a program that @{b}ALLWAYS@{ub} shows the right cpu-time @{b}ANYTIME@{ub}.
This program is great if you want to find out if your (or any) program takes too much cpu-time.
And if so, you want to reduce it.

Now, there is only 1 version. Normally when you haven't got sysinfo/sysmon.library or didn't run StartSM,
the old routine kicks in. However if you do have them and run StartSM, IdleA68K will use the routine from the sysmon package.

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements for Idle A68K"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Requirements"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

@{b}Idle A68K@{ub} requires an Amiga with at least @{b}V44 (OS 3.5)@{ub} and not too much memory.
If you wanna use arexx, you also need @{b}arexx.class@{ub}
For using the sysmon routine, you @{b}@{u}need@{uu}@{ub} sysinfo.library/sysmon.library & StartSM.
If you wanna use ScreenNotify, install screennotify.library 1.x in libs:

@endnode

@node "History" "Idle A68K History"
@next "History"
@prev "History"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}History@{ub}@{uu}
@{JLEFT}
 V1.01-1.023     -  For internal use only.
 V1.024 & 1.027  -  First public release.
 V1.100  28/01/2001 - New GUI (GTLayout).
 V1.101  01/02/2001 - Made the response a bit better.
 V1.102  15/02/2001 - Fixed some enforcer hits. Code cleanup. Added tooltype TEN.
 V1.103  19/02/2001 - Small fix.
 V1.104  20/02/2001 - Kicked 1 patchwork hit out. Added 'text in gauge'.
 V1.105  27/02/2001 - Added CPU check routine. Added tooltype for 'text in gauge'.
 V1.65   22/12/2002 - Made a Reaction GUI for the A68K version, so it looks the same as the WOS version.
                      Bumped the version to 1.65 to be inline with the WOS version.
 V1.65b  31/05/2003 - Added an experimental version which uses sysinfo.library.
 V1.65c1 06/06/2003 - Recompiled the old version with VBCC. Should now work on all A68K emulators too.
 V1.66b  08/03/2005 - Added Arexx. Now some limited commands are possible. Kicked the experimental version.
 V1.66d  23/03/2005 - On popular demand, included the experimental version again ;)
 V1.66d  25/08/2005 - Recompiled with VBCC 0.8i.
 V1.66d  07/05/2006 - Maintenance update.
 V1.68   18/05/2006 - Added vertical gauge bar. Fixed some bugs in window handling.
 V1.69   21/05/2006 - Added automatic switch between the old routine and sysmon.library. If you haven't got sysmon or
                      didn't run StartSM, the program will make use of the old routine.
 V1.70   18/12/2006 - Added support for ScreenNotify.
 V1.70b  18/01/2007 - Removed bug that made uniconifying impossible.
 V1.70d  26/03/09   - Small changes. Should work just a little better with WinUAE. Recompiled with vbcc 0.9.

@endnode

